# GhosttyKit build products (tools/build-ghostty.sh output — never committed).
# Anchored to the repo root: unanchored `vendor/` also swallowed
# Sources/AgentCoding/Vendor/ (vendored source that IS committed).
# No trailing slash: `/vendor/` matched only a directory, so a dev setup
# where vendor is a SYMLINK (e.g. into a shared worktree) wasn't ignored —
# that's how a dangling absolute symlink got committed and broke fresh CI
# checkouts once.
/vendor
